  "prompt": "What is a store credit?",
  "response": "Store credit is a form of currency that a retailer offers to a customer, typically in the event of a return or exchange of merchandise. Instead of receiving a refund in cash or back to their original payment method, the customer is issued a credit that can be used to make purchases at that particular store or chain. \n\nStore credits can come in various forms, such as a physical gift card, a digital code, or an account balance that the customer can redeem in future transactions. The amount of store credit is generally equivalent to the value of the returned item, and there may be terms and conditions associated with its use, such as expiration dates or restrictions on certain products. Store credit is often used by retailers as a way to retain customers and encourage them to continue shopping at their store.",
